A phthalic acid monoester resulting from the formal condensation of one of the carboxy groups of phthalic acid with cyclohexanol. It is a metabolite of the commonly used plasticiser dicyclohexyl phthalate.

A phthalic acid monoester resulting from the formal condensation of one of the carboxy groups of phthalic acid with the hydroxy group of benzyl alcohol. It is a major metabolite of the plasticiser butyl benzyl phthalate (BBP).
